The paper deals with matrix completion, a problem that is commonly studied in machine learning and computer vision, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions sample complexity, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and the use of fast updates, which could be related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
